item.title: Extremely strange things about Eli!
item.dc:creator: Fuskox
item.description:
sudpuzzer:

I dunno, I just re watched the ending to EP2 and I think it’s pretty straightforward: the first advisor comes in and pushes everyone down, and the isolates Eli by keeping Gordon and Alyx pushed against the wall, because killing one puny human in relative safety makes more sense than trying to kill all 3 at once. It was just taking it’s time, thinking it had the situation well controlled. It took a moment to study Gordon and Alyx, and didn’t appear to notice Eli getting up. After getting whacked, the advisor simply knocked him over and let the second on finish him off. Then, the first proceeded to kill Alyx. They were simply killing in a cold, calculated methodical way that seems characteristic of the combine, which of course gets interrupted. There’s really no deeper meaning to it. It’s the same way as the barn advisor methodically observes its surroundings. Once it is done with one object, it is discarded, and the advisor moves on to the next item.

@Tosser: What in the fuck are you on, cuz I want some

Yeah, people really over-analyze too much when they have long waits for things. They were just killing them, maybe they extract information out of people when they kill them with their tongues, but idk.

Read full topic
